Detailed Description

cvmx_pko_mem_queue_qos

Notes: Sets the QOS mask, per queue. These QOS_MASK bits are logically and physically the same QOS_MASK bits in PKO_MEM_QUEUE_PTRS. This CSR address allows the QOS_MASK bits to be written during PKO operation without affecting any other queue state. The port to which queue QID is mapped is port PID. Note that the queue to port mapping must be the same as was previously programmed via the PKO_MEM_QUEUE_PTRS CSR. This CSR is a memory of 256 entries, and thus, the PKO_REG_READ_IDX CSR must be written before any CSR read operations to this address can be performed. A read of any entry that has not been previously written is illegal and will result in unpredictable CSR read data.
